# GTX Core

> The central backend platform powering the GTX W3DA ecosystem.

GTX Core is the foundational backend infrastructure that connects every product in the GTX ecosystem. It provides a unified API layer, authentication, business logic, data management, and integrations required to operate secure and scalable digital asset services.

---

# Overview

GTX Core is designed as a modular platform that serves as the operational backbone for the ecosystem. Rather than each product maintaining its own backend, GTX Core exposes shared services through a centralized architecture.

Products such as GTX AI, GTX OTC, GTX Wallet, and the GTX Website communicate with GTX Core through secure APIs.

---

# Architecture

```
                    GTX Website
                          │
                    GTX AI Platform
                          │
                    GTX Wallet
                          │
                    GTX OTC
                          │
               ─────────────────────
                     GTX Core API
               ─────────────────────
          Authentication & Authorization
          User Management
          Wallet Services
          Market Services
          Settlement Engine
          Notification Service
          Audit & Logging
          Database Layer
               ─────────────────────
          External Providers
          • Payment Providers
          • Market Data Providers
          • Blockchain Networks
```

GTX Core follows a modular service-oriented architecture, allowing new services to be added without disrupting existing functionality.

